    • Method Detail

      • addMember

        public static void addMember()
        Prompts the user for information on a member, which then is funneled into a MemberData constructor. The new MemberData object is then stored into the arraylist.

      • deleteMember

        public static void deleteMember()
        Prompts the user for a member number, and then deletes the MemberData object from the arraylist that corresponds with that number.

      • updateMember

        public static void updateMember()
        Prompts the user to input a member number, after which the user is prompted to edit a certain field of the MemberData which corresponds to the given member number.

      • validateMember

        public static boolean validateMember()
        Prompts a the user for a member number, then checks to see if that member number corresponds to any MemberData which exists in the array list.
        Returns:
        true if there exists a MemberData object which corresponds to the given member number

      • validateCode

        public static boolean validateCode​(java.lang.String memberCode)
        Similar to the above verification function, however this method simply accepts a String as a parameter and returns whether or not it's a valid member number without prompting the user or confirming/denying the validation through a print method.
        Parameters:
        memberCode - a member number which may or may not be validated
        Returns:
        true if memberCode is an existent member number

      • addService

        public static void addService​(java.lang.String memberNumber,
                              ServiceData newService)
        Adds a service to the corresponding MemberData
        Parameters:
        memberNumber - given member number used to isolate the MemberData object that will have a service added to it
        newService - the service to be added

      • getMemberList

        public static java.util.ArrayList<MemberData> getMemberList()
        Get function for the ArrayList which corresponds to the members who are a part of the ChocAn network.
        Returns:
        the arraylist which stores the MemberData objects that correspond to the members
